snippet: As a pivotal decision-maker on a proposal to expand Chelsea Market, the City Council speaker, Christine C. Quinn, is facing pressure from big campaign donors and neighborhood loyalists.
abstract: City Council Speaker and mayoral candidate Christine C Quinn faces pressure from big campaign donors and neighborhood loyalists over Chelsea Market expansion proposal; proposal is enthusiastically supported by Mayor Michael R Bloomberg and overseers of the High Line, but various organizations, neighborhood leaders and local political groups object to zoning exemptions that they believe undermine the will of the community.
lead_paragraph: As a pivotal decision-maker on a proposal to expand Chelsea Market, the City Council speaker, Christine C. Quinn, is facing pressure from big campaign donors and neighborhood loyalists.

headline.seo: Amid Din of Chelsea Market Plan, Silence From Christine C. Quinn
headline.main: Mayoral Hopes Seen as Muting Quinn's Voice
headline.print_headline: Mayoral Hopes Seen as Muting Fighter’s Voice
